\dfrac{x^2}{(x-1)(x+1)^2}
\dfrac{x^2}{(x-1)(x+1)^2} = \dfrac{A}{x-1} + \dfrac{B}{x+1} + \dfrac{C}{(x+1)^2}
 x^2 = A(x+1)^3 + B(x-1)(x+1)^2 + C(x+1)(x-1)
 0 = A - B - C 
x = 1
1 = A + 0B + 0C
A = 1
x = -1
1 = 0A + 0B + 0C
1 = 0
x^2=A(x+1)^2+B(x-1)(x+1)+C(x-1)
\;x=1\;
1^2=A\cdot2^2\implies A=\frac14
\;x=-1\;
